<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>The eBay Scandal Gets a Thriller-Like Documentary</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/13/technology/ebay-documentary-scandal-whatever-it-takes.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/13/technology/ebay-documentary-scandal-whatever-it-takes.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/13/technology/ebay-documentary-scandal-whatever-it-takes.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A newly available documentary, ‘Whatever It Takes,’ examines eBay workers’ plot to cyberstalk journalists and critics.</description><dc:creator>David Streitfeld</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 09:01:42 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">eBay</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Whatever It Takes: Inside the eBay Scandal</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">E Commerce</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberharassment</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Online harassment</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">cyberbullies</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">online trolls</category><category domai